    <sub><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemical_specificity">source</a>, image modified to add white bg</sub><br>
    <h3>pH</h3>
    <p>
        - The optimum pH for most enzymes is 7, but in more acidic conditions it can be lower
        (like 2 pH in the stomach) and higher in more alkaline conditions (like 8 to 9 in the duodenum and mouth).<br>
        - If the pH is too high or low, the bonds that hold the amino acid chains together (which 
        make up the protein) will be destroyed, and denaturation can occur.
    </p>
